&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Purpose&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Ecommerce Manager for DACH &amp;amp; ROW&lt;/strong&gt;, you are responsible for driving commercial growth across Travix’s direct-to-consumer business in the region. You combine strong market understanding, commercial thinking, and a growth mindset to identify and unlock opportunities across traffic, conversion, partnerships, and new customer acquisition channels.This role reports directly to the E-Commerce Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with Performance Marketing, Affiliate Marketing, CRM, Pricing, Partnerships, Brand teams to build market-specific growth plans, optimize commercial performance, and explore new revenue and acquisition opportunities. With a strong focus on the German market, you translate consumer, competitor, and market insights into clear initiatives that drive sustainable growth, margin improvement, and stronger brand performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The main goal&lt;/strong&gt; of this role is to &lt;strong&gt;drive sustainable growth across DACH &amp;amp; ROW &lt;/strong&gt;by identifying market opportunities, building strong growth plans, expanding customer acquisition channels, and creating commercial opportunities through data-driven execution, partnerships, and cross-functional collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Act as the commercial owner of DACH &amp;amp; ROW markets&lt;/strong&gt;, driving regionally relevant growth initiatives while owning market performance and P&amp;amp;L in close collaboration with Pricing, E-Commerce, Finance, and Commercial teams. Bring strong knowledge of German/DACH consumer behavior, competitive dynamics, and market opportunities to optimize revenue, margin, conversion, and long-term growth through data-driven execution and performance tracking.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Take ownership of the end-to-end customer journey&lt;/strong&gt; across DACH &amp;amp; ROW, identifying opportunities to improve UX, conversion, and customer value. Work closely with Product and Tech teams to prioritize and drive developments that enhance customer experience, scalability, and commercial performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead growth planning and execution&lt;/strong&gt; by developing market-specific growth plans based on consumer behavior, competitive trends, seasonality, and commercial opportunities to drive traffic, conversion, customer acquisition, and contribution margin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coordinate market acquisition growth initiatives&lt;/strong&gt; by working closely with Performance Marketing, Affiliate Marketing, CRM, SEO, and broader commercial teams to identify, test, and scale high-impact growth opportunities, ensuring strong alignment between market priorities, channel strategies, and commercial objectives while maximizing efficiency and ROI.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive partnerships and new growth opportunities&lt;/strong&gt; by identifying and building strategic partnerships that increase traffic, brand visibility, customer acquisition, and revenue growth, while exploring new scalable channels and commercial opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own content excellence and local market relevance&lt;/strong&gt; by ensuring strong localization, content quality, campaign execution, and alignment of messaging, promotions, and customer experience with DACH &amp;amp; ROW market needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the table&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in growth, e-commerce, digital marketing, commercial strategy, performance marketing, or online business development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of the German/DACH market, consumer behavior, and regional commercial dynamics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven

&lt;p&gt;As the&lt;strong&gt; E-Commerce &amp;amp; Pricing Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;, you play a key role in driving growth and profitability across Travix’s direct-to-consumer e-commerce channel. You support the E-Commerce Director and wider Direct team with data-driven insights and recommendations across website performance, pricing, conversion, revenue, campaigns, and contribution margin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with teams across E-Commerce, Pricing, Finance, Marketing, and Supply, you turn complex data into clear business actions that help improve pricing competitiveness, optimize conversion, maximize ROI, and support smarter commercial decisions across our key markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The main goal &lt;/strong&gt;of this role is to &lt;strong&gt;drive commercial growth and margin optimization&lt;/strong&gt; by delivering data-driven insights across pricing, demand, supply, conversion, portfolio performance, and market opportunities, while building scalable analytical capabilities through dashboards, forecasting, AI, automation, and advanced analytics to enable smarter pricing, revenue, and commercial decision-making.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver clear,&lt;strong&gt; data-driven insights&lt;/strong&gt; across markets, channels, pricing, conversion, demand, supply, and key commercial performance drivers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive &lt;strong&gt;margin optimization and commercial growth&lt;/strong&gt; by analyzing demand- and supply-driven segmentation, portfolio performance, pricing opportunities, customer behavior, and market gaps using analytical models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct &lt;strong&gt;portfolio segmentation, gap analysis, price elasticity analysis, and forecasting&lt;/strong&gt; to identify growth opportunities, pricing inefficiencies, and revenue improvement levers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and optimize &lt;strong&gt;dashboards, forecasting models, and analytical frameworks&lt;/strong&gt;, leveraging &lt;strong&gt;AI, automation, and advanced analytics&lt;/strong&gt; to monitor key business KPIs, improve efficiency, uncover deeper insights, and support smarter pricing, commercial, and revenue-related decision-making across traffic, conversion, revenue, orders, pricing competitiveness, contribution margin, and profitability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to the table&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of experience in data, business, e-commerce, pricing, revenue management, commercial analytics, or performance analysis, ideally in e-commerce, travel, marketplaces, retail, or performance marketing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of digital funnels, pricing dynamics, merchandising, conversion optimization, commercial KPIs, and profitability drivers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills with the ability to connect pricing, traffic, conversion, revenue, marketing activity, and margin performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with large datasets and translating complex analysis into clear business recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with pricing analysis, revenue management, price competitiveness, elasticity, margin optimization, forecasting, or commercial planning is a strong plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with BI and visualization tools (e.g. Looker, Tableau, Power BI).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic to intermediate skills in SQL, Python, and/or R are a strong plus. Experience with rule-based machine learning models and time series analysis is an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in Google Analytics 4 (GA4) for tracking website traffic, user behavior, and standard reporting is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English; other European languages are a plus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you can expect from us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
