&lt;p&gt;Step into a world where data and creativity come together, and where your work directly impacts how millions of travelers book their journeys. As a Marketing &amp;amp; E-commerce Intern at Travix, you will dive into the dynamic world of website optimization, content management, and digital growth for brands like Flugladen.de and CheapTickets.ch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is your opportunity to learn how international travel brands operate behind the scenes and to make a real impact on our upcoming campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are we looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic Marketing &amp;amp; E-commerce Intern for a period of 6 months. You are curious, creative, eager to learn, and enjoy a challenge. With your data-driven mindset, creative thinking, and hands-on attitude, you will thrive in a fast-paced, international environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Marketing &amp;amp; E-commerce Intern, you will play an active role in shaping the experience travelers have when booking their next adventure. Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting content management and content strategy, including involvement in executing campaign plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with website optimization and learning how it impacts customer journeys and conversion rates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with the Partnerships team to manage relationships with airlines and other partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning how to create performance analyses and reports, and translating them into actionable insights for optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing creative ideas to improve the online travel experience across the website and social media&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exploring how AI can be applied effectively across different processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What do you bring?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills (both written and verbal)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, hands-on mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical thinking and an interest in data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creativity and attention to detail, with an affinity for social media and trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in marketing and the travel industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in AI and new technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in a Bachelor’s or Master’s program during the internship period&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability to work 2–3 days per week from the office (Amsterdam Bijlmer)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English is a must. Fluent in German is a big advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What do we offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid working with flexibility and a healthy work-life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work abroad for a few days (upon agreement)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An open and informal work environment where your ideas matter&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An international team with over 50 nationalities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel expense reimbursement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A modern and vibrant office in Amsterdam Bijlmer Arena&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free fruit, snacks, team outings, and events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Travix&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travix is one of the world’s largest online travel organizations, with brands such as CheapTickets, Vliegwinkel, and BudgetAir. As part of Trip.com Group, we operate globally in more than 40 countries. Our mission? To make travel accessible anytime, anywhere.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ready to make an impact in the world of online travel? Apply now and start your journey with Travix!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an enthusiastic &lt;strong&gt;Partnerships Marketing Intern&lt;/strong&gt; to join our global online marketing team in Amsterdam. This role is ideal for someone eager to gain hands-on experience at the intersection of &lt;strong&gt;content marketing and partnerships&lt;/strong&gt;, supporting international campaigns across multiple markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll play a key role in bringing partner campaigns to life, from content creation to execution and performance tracking, while learning how strategic partnerships drive growth in a fast-paced digital environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Partnerships Marketing Intern, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the &lt;strong&gt;end-to-end execution of partner marketing campaigns&lt;/strong&gt;, from setup to reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create engaging &lt;strong&gt;content and campaign assets&lt;/strong&gt; aligned with brand guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in &lt;strong&gt;activating campaigns&lt;/strong&gt;, monitoring performance, and ensuring everything runs smoothly (including capturing live campaign placements)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help &lt;strong&gt;analyze campaign performance&lt;/strong&gt; using tools such as Google Analytics and internal platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team in &lt;strong&gt;prospecting and researching new partners and business opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the broader marketing team on cross-channel initiatives (e.g. newsletters, internal channels).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll learn&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The fundamentals of &lt;strong&gt;partnership marketing and campaign operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How to create impactful content for &lt;strong&gt;international partner campaigns&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insights into the &lt;strong&gt;travel and airline industry&lt;/strong&gt;, one of the most dynamic global markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent in English; proficiency in Dutch is preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in a relevant degree (e.g. Marketing, Communication, Journalism) for the full internship duration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available full-time for &lt;strong&gt;at least 6 months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in the Netherlands and enrolled at a Dutch university&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organized, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple tasks and deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, hands-on mindset with eagerness to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative with strong writing and storytelling skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in travel and digital marketing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of design tools (e.g. Photoshop, Canva) is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;hands-on internship&lt;/strong&gt; with real responsibilities from day one&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship and guidance from experienced marketing professionals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to &lt;strong&gt;develop practical skills in digital marketing and partnerships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative, international team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Room for creativity, ownership, and bringing your ideas to life&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A company laptop for the duration of your internship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fun team events and a supportive workplace culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internship allowance of €750 (gross).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
